  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Adventist Development and Relief Agency (ADRA) works to improve the quality of life for people in need all over the world. ADRA invests in the potential of individuals through advocacy, supporting families, promoting health, providing food and water, establishing livelihoods, and responding to emergencies. 

ADRA is instituting the Mulungi School Project in the heart of the Lugela and Mocuba districts of the Zambezia province. The project is developing a self-sustaining institution that provides a comprehensive education to the people of Mozambique. The 500 children who attend the school receive high quality schooling along with a daily meal, vocational instruction and more. The project also integrates an agricultural program for self-sufficiency and builds local infrastructure to holistically improve the community.</narrative>
  </description>
